         <abstract>
            <p>Let K be a totally real algebraic number field and O an order in a quaternion algebra U over K. Assume that the group O&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; of units in O with reduced norm equal to 1 is embedded into PSL&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt; (R) as an arithmetic Fuchsian group. It is shown how Ford's algorithm can be effectively applied in order to determine a fundamental domain of O&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt; as well as a complete system of generators of O&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;.</p>
          </abstract>
